A man who lost an incredible 390lbs just through good old-fashioned diet and exercise, and beat his chronic alcoholism without any treatment or support, has turned to a crowdsourcing website to help him with the final part of his journey.

Brian Flemming, a 32-year-old music teacher from Canton, Michigan, is now barely recognizable as the 625lb man he used to be - but his massive weight loss has left with him between 30 and 40lbs of excess skin.

'It's a constant reminder of my past and it gets in my way every single day,' Mr Flemming, who is asking for $22,000 in donations for skin removal surgery via GoFundMe, tells Daily Mail Online.

